  "prompt": "What are some best songs to listen to?",
  "response": "Choosing the best songs to listen to can be quite subjective, as it depends on your personal taste and mood. However, here are some popular and critically acclaimed songs across various genres that might appeal to different preferences:\n\n### Pop:\n1. **\"Blinding Lights\" by The Weeknd**\n2. **\"Levitating\" by Dua Lipa**\n3. **\"Shape of You\" by Ed Sheeran**\n4. **\"Bad Guy\" by Billie Eilish**\n5. **\"Watermelon Sugar\" by Harry Styles**\n\n### Rock:\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen**\n2. **\"Hotel California\" by Eagles**\n3. **\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" by Nirvana**\n4. **\"Stairway to Heaven\" by Led Zeppelin**\n5. **\"Sweet Child O' Mine\" by Guns N' Roses**\n\n### Hip-Hop/Rap:\n1. **\"Sicko Mode\" by Travis Scott**\n2. **\"God's Plan\" by Drake**\n3. **\"Lose Yourself\" by Eminem**\n4. **\"Old Town Road\" by Lil Nas X**\n5. **\"Stronger\" by Kanye West**\n\n### R&B:\n1. **\"Adore You\" by Harry Styles**\n2. **\"Blinding Lights\" by The Weeknd**\n3. **\"No Guidance\" by Chris Brown ft. Drake**\n4. **\"All of Me\" by John Legend**\n5. **\"Earned It\" by The Weeknd**\n\n### Electronic/Dance:\n1. **\"Titanium\" by David Guetta ft. Sia**\n2. **\"Wake Me Up\" by Avicii**\n3. **\"Don't You Worry Child\" by Swedish House Mafia**\n4. **\"Closer\" by The Chainsmokers ft. Halsey**\n5. **\"Levels\" by Avicii**\n\n### Classical:\n1. **\"Clair de Lune\" by Claude Debussy**\n2. **\"Fur Elise\" by Ludwig van Beethoven**\n3. **\"The Four Seasons\" by Antonio Vivaldi**\n4. **\"Canon in D Major\" by Johann Pachelbel**\n5. **\"Nocturne in E-flat Major\" by Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin**\n\n### Jazz:\n1. **\"Take Five\" by Dave Brubeck**\n2. **\"So What\" by Miles Davis**\n3. **\"Sing, Sing, Sing\" by Benny Goodman**\n4. **\"What a Wonderful World\" by Louis Armstrong**\n5. **\"Blue in Green\" by Miles Davis**\n\n### Indie/Alternative:\n1. **\"Take Me Out\" by Franz Ferdinand**\n2. **\"Dog Days Are Over\" by Florence + The Machine**\n3. **\"Mr. Brightside\" by The Killers**\n4. **\"Little Lion Man\" by Mumford & Sons**\n5. **\"Riptide\" by Vance Joy**\n\nThese are just a few suggestions, and there are countless other songs out there that might resonate with you. Feel free to explore different genres and artists to find what you love most!",
